WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.964 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.964 --> 00:00:14.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:17.500 align:middle line:10%
>> Voices From The Inside Out--

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:21.080 align:middle line:10%
Innerviews: A Different
Kind of Talk Television.

00:00:21.080 --> 00:00:25.990 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:28.880 align:middle line:84%
>> The Buddha basically
was a revolutionary.

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:30.800 align:middle line:84%
And he revolutionized
the Indian society,

00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:33.570 align:middle line:84%
and Buddhism revolutionized
every society where it went.

00:00:33.570 --> 00:00:35.960 align:middle line:84%
But the reason why
people haven't noticed

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:39.290 align:middle line:84%
was that it wasn't what we
would call a hot revolution,

00:00:39.290 --> 00:00:40.430 align:middle line:90%
like Lenin or something.

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:41.780 align:middle line:90%
It was a cool revolution.

00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:45.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Robert Thurman is arguably
the most respected Buddhist

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:47.300 align:middle line:90%
scholar in the West.

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:50.960 align:middle line:84%
In 1998, no less a
personage than His Holiness

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:54.050 align:middle line:84%
the Dalai Lama, Thurman's
friend and teacher,

00:00:54.050 --> 00:00:56.960 align:middle line:84%
helped to dedicate
Tibet House in New York.

00:00:56.960 --> 00:00:59.870 align:middle line:84%
Not only is Thurmond president
of that organization,

00:00:59.870 --> 00:01:02.750 align:middle line:84%
but he's also a prolific
author and the head

00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:05.730 align:middle line:84%
of the Department of Religion
at Columbia University.

00:01:05.730 --> 00:01:08.180 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:01:08.180 --> 00:01:12.410 align:middle line:90%


00:01:12.410 --> 00:01:14.600 align:middle line:84%
>> He's also an outspoken
advocate for the plight

00:01:14.600 --> 00:01:17.930 align:middle line:84%
of the Tibetans, whose homeland
was overrun by the Chinese

00:01:17.930 --> 00:01:20.330 align:middle line:90%
in 1959.

00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:24.140 align:middle line:10%
These Tibetan monks, ,
performing recently in Phoenix

00:01:24.140 --> 00:01:27.530 align:middle line:10%
were driven from their centuries
old monastery and-- along with

00:01:27.530 --> 00:01:29.420 align:middle line:10%
their leader, the Dalai Lama--

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:32.300 align:middle line:10%
remain in exile.

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:34.790 align:middle line:84%
Thurman says that
political activism,

00:01:34.790 --> 00:01:38.720 align:middle line:84%
perhaps an unexpected quality
among gentle Buddhists,

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:40.850 align:middle line:84%
is a natural outgrowth
of what it really

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:42.860 align:middle line:90%
means to be a Buddhist.

00:01:42.860 --> 00:01:46.992 align:middle line:84%
My illuminating conversation
with Robert began there.

00:01:46.992 --> 00:01:49.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Mr. Thurman, what a
pleasure to sit down with you.

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:51.492 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's a great pleasure
to be with you, Chantal.

00:01:51.492 --> 00:01:52.820 align:middle line:90%
>> I thank you.

00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:55.760 align:middle line:10%
Because the Buddhist way--

00:01:55.760 --> 00:01:57.530 align:middle line:10%
to the best of my knowledge--

00:01:57.530 --> 00:02:01.420 align:middle line:10%
is a simple way, let's begin
with a simple question.

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.230 align:middle line:90%
What is a Buddhist?

00:02:03.230 --> 00:02:04.170 align:middle line:90%
>> What is a Buddhist?

00:02:04.170 --> 00:02:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:04.970 --> 00:02:07.970 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, a Buddhist can be
pretty much whatever they want

00:02:07.970 --> 00:02:10.928 align:middle line:10%
to be, you could
say, in general.

00:02:10.928 --> 00:02:12.470 align:middle line:10%
Technically, you
would say a Buddhist

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:16.070 align:middle line:10%
is a person who has taken
refuge in the Three Jewels--

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:17.480 align:middle line:10%
of the Buddha,
who is the teacher

00:02:17.480 --> 00:02:19.670 align:middle line:10%
of the way to
enlightenment, the Dharma,

00:02:19.670 --> 00:02:21.800 align:middle line:10%
which is enlightenment
itself and the reality

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:25.730 align:middle line:10%
that underlies it and the
reality that unfolds our lives,

00:02:25.730 --> 00:02:28.540 align:middle line:10%
and the Sangha is
the community that--

00:02:28.540 --> 00:02:31.190 align:middle line:10%
of those who are
seeking that same way.

00:02:31.190 --> 00:02:33.260 align:middle line:84%
So a Buddhist is one
who has taken refuge

00:02:33.260 --> 00:02:35.060 align:middle line:90%
with those Three Jewels.

00:02:35.060 --> 00:02:38.090 align:middle line:84%
They're jewels because they're
so valuable and rare in sort

00:02:38.090 --> 00:02:41.570 align:middle line:84%
of the ocean of life's
possibilities, you could say.

00:02:41.570 --> 00:02:42.500 align:middle line:90%
That's a Buddhist.

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:47.600 align:middle line:84%
>> It is interesting to me
that, despite the huge variety

00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:52.640 align:middle line:84%
of religions we have in
America, and so of them so old

00:02:52.640 --> 00:02:58.580 align:middle line:84%
and so powerful, so strong, so
many millions of Americans are

00:02:58.580 --> 00:03:00.770 align:middle line:84%
attracted to
Buddhism these days?

00:03:00.770 --> 00:03:02.720 align:middle line:90%
Why do you suppose that is?

00:03:02.720 --> 00:03:05.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think because
Buddhism is basically a way

00:03:05.930 --> 00:03:07.640 align:middle line:90%
to freedom.

00:03:07.640 --> 00:03:10.100 align:middle line:84%
The reason you take refuge
in those Three Jewels

00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:13.850 align:middle line:84%
is that you want to find
freedom from suffering, freedom

00:03:13.850 --> 00:03:16.400 align:middle line:84%
from sort of being
caught automatically

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:19.550 align:middle line:84%
in involuntary responses
and sort of bondage

00:03:19.550 --> 00:03:23.550 align:middle line:84%
to this and that drives and
reactions and things like that.

00:03:23.550 --> 00:03:26.560 align:middle line:84%
And people in America, we
sort of admire freedom.

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:29.930 align:middle line:84%
It's a constitutional right of
ours to have it and seek it.

00:03:29.930 --> 00:03:32.130 align:middle line:84%
We don't really doesn't
know what it is,

00:03:32.130 --> 00:03:34.280 align:middle line:84%
but we vaguely feel that
if we have more of it

00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:35.150 align:middle line:90%
we'll be more happy.

00:03:35.150 --> 00:03:35.950 align:middle line:90%


00:03:35.950 --> 00:03:38.780 align:middle line:84%
And so since Buddhism is a
sort of technical, inner way

00:03:38.780 --> 00:03:42.518 align:middle line:84%
to freedom, it kind of fits
with our sense of the outer--

00:03:42.518 --> 00:03:44.060 align:middle line:84%
the outer world,
you know, our notion

00:03:44.060 --> 00:03:46.710 align:middle line:84%
of political freedom and
freedom of the individual,

00:03:46.710 --> 00:03:47.510 align:middle line:90%
this sort of thing.

00:03:47.510 --> 00:03:49.610 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism is very,
very suited for that.

00:03:49.610 --> 00:03:51.680 align:middle line:84%
It's a method of
how to achieve that.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.110 align:middle line:90%
And people are attracted to it.

00:03:54.110 --> 00:03:56.870 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, Chantal, most
of the Buddhist groups

00:03:56.870 --> 00:04:00.860 align:middle line:84%
are not active proselytizers
or missionaries.

00:04:00.860 --> 00:04:03.620 align:middle line:84%
And they don't seek to
just increase their numbers

00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:06.920 align:middle line:84%
by enrolling a lot of people
nominally in the Buddhist

00:04:06.920 --> 00:04:07.880 align:middle line:90%
orders.

00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:10.580 align:middle line:84%
And so we're not making a
big campaign or something

00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:12.652 align:middle line:84%
like that, which
I think would be--

00:04:12.652 --> 00:04:14.360 align:middle line:84%
would be-- it's the
wrong type of history

00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:17.390 align:middle line:84%
to go around and have
religious competition, I think.

00:04:17.390 --> 00:04:20.029 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, there seem to
be so many different kinds

00:04:20.029 --> 00:04:20.899 align:middle line:90%
of Buddhist groups.

00:04:20.899 --> 00:04:22.670 align:middle line:84%
Just in Los Angeles,
where I live,

00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:25.620 align:middle line:84%
there are so many
different Buddhist sects.

00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:26.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:04:26.420 --> 00:04:27.500 align:middle line:90%
Mm-hmm.

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Does that concern you, or
does it concern His Holiness,

00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:35.430 align:middle line:84%
that the essence of Buddhism
will be lost when there are

00:04:35.430 --> 00:04:36.830 align:middle line:90%
so many different kinds?

00:04:36.830 --> 00:04:37.970 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I don't think so.

00:04:37.970 --> 00:04:39.620 align:middle line:84%
There have always been
many different kinds.

00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:41.412 align:middle line:84%
You know, the early
teaching of the Buddha,

00:04:41.412 --> 00:04:44.750 align:middle line:84%
the monastic teaching, divided
into 18 different orders,

00:04:44.750 --> 00:04:46.850 align:middle line:84%
based on minor things
like whether or not

00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:49.310 align:middle line:84%
you could have three ounces
of salt in your wallet

00:04:49.310 --> 00:04:51.170 align:middle line:84%
or not as a monk,
minor sort of thing,

00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:55.400 align:middle line:84%
whether, when a monk had a wet
dream, it was a sin or not--

00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:56.917 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes, yes.

00:04:56.917 --> 00:04:59.000 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's just human
nature, I think, Chantal.

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.190 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't worry His Holiness.

00:05:01.190 --> 00:05:04.070 align:middle line:84%
Actually, His Holiness has
an attitude, the Dalai Lama,

00:05:04.070 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:84%
and a formal policy,
which he states regularly,

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:08.900 align:middle line:84%
that he would prefer
not to convert

00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:10.580 align:middle line:90%
many people to Buddhism.

00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:13.370 align:middle line:84%
And he hopes that Christians
will remain Christians, Jews,

00:05:13.370 --> 00:05:15.920 align:middle line:90%
Jews, humanists, humanists.

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:19.220 align:middle line:84%
But if they can find anything of
value from Buddhist meditation,

00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:22.340 align:middle line:84%
Buddhist philosophy or
psychology, Buddhist ethics,

00:05:22.340 --> 00:05:24.590 align:middle line:84%
by all means, make
use of it, but stay

00:05:24.590 --> 00:05:28.100 align:middle line:84%
within their own sort of ritual
and denominational matrix

00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:30.410 align:middle line:84%
with their families
and their traditions

00:05:30.410 --> 00:05:33.410 align:middle line:84%
so as to avoid stress and
conflict in their lives.

00:05:33.410 --> 00:05:35.540 align:middle line:84%
Only the very few
who, at some point,

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:37.790 align:middle line:84%
decide they want to really
meditate in an advanced way

00:05:37.790 --> 00:05:39.290 align:middle line:84%
or do something
like that, he thinks

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:40.310 align:middle line:84%
then, if they wish,
then, of course,

00:05:40.310 --> 00:05:42.330 align:middle line:84%
they should be free
in a free country.

00:05:42.330 --> 00:05:45.530 align:middle line:84%
But he doesn't encourage people
to shift denomination and as

00:05:45.530 --> 00:05:47.843 align:middle line:84%
if that would solve
their problems.

00:05:47.843 --> 00:05:49.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Speaking of meditation
in the Buddhist way,

00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:54.530 align:middle line:84%
I have a wonderful friend who is
a devout Buddhist, Jamie Otis.

00:05:54.530 --> 00:05:56.120 align:middle line:90%
On Sundays, he is silent.

00:05:56.120 --> 00:05:57.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm, that's right.

00:05:57.540 --> 00:05:59.630 align:middle line:84%
>> In fact, I think he's
writing a book called--

00:05:59.630 --> 00:06:01.070 align:middle line:90%
let's give Jamie a plug.

00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:03.510 align:middle line:84%
He's writing a book called
"Silent Sundays, One Man's

00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:03.990 align:middle line:90%
Journey."

00:06:03.990 --> 00:06:04.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, really?

00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:05.540 align:middle line:84%
I didn't actually realize
that he was actually

00:06:05.540 --> 00:06:06.415 align:middle line:90%
writing it as a book.

00:06:06.415 --> 00:06:07.670 align:middle line:90%
But I knew they have it.

00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:08.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, there's talk of it.

00:06:08.910 --> 00:06:09.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:09.710 --> 00:06:11.543 align:middle line:84%
>> And his habit is to
be completely silent.

00:06:11.543 --> 00:06:12.343 align:middle line:90%
>> That's true.

00:06:12.343 --> 00:06:13.193 align:middle line:90%
He is.

00:06:13.193 --> 00:06:14.110 align:middle line:90%
He really does it too.

00:06:14.110 --> 00:06:17.340 align:middle line:84%
He writes you notes if you
try to say something to him.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:19.090 align:middle line:84%
>> And you know, because
I'm around Jamie,

00:06:19.090 --> 00:06:20.257 align:middle line:90%
I try it every now and then.

00:06:20.257 --> 00:06:21.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's hard.

00:06:21.190 --> 00:06:21.685 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:21.685 --> 00:06:22.510 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:06:22.510 --> 00:06:23.320 align:middle line:90%
>> It's very hard.

00:06:23.320 --> 00:06:23.935 align:middle line:90%
>> It's good, though.

00:06:23.935 --> 00:06:25.300 align:middle line:90%
It makes you think about things.

00:06:25.300 --> 00:06:27.560 align:middle line:84%
He communicates with his
gestures, his expressions,

00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:28.360 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:28.870 align:middle line:90%
Well, you've noticed that.

00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:29.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:30.670 align:middle line:90%
>> It's wonderful.

00:06:30.670 --> 00:06:35.830 align:middle line:84%
>> So my question to you is,
what does silence bring to us?

00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:38.080 align:middle line:84%
Because I know it is very
often the Buddhist way

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:41.500 align:middle line:84%
to meditate in silence, to be
silent, as our friend Jamie is.

00:06:41.500 --> 00:06:42.300 align:middle line:90%
What gift--

00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:44.340 align:middle line:84%
Well, but sometimes we
do have type A Buddhists.

00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:45.480 align:middle line:90%
I am one of them.

00:06:45.480 --> 00:06:46.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Aha.

00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:47.710 align:middle line:90%
>> I am a noisy Buddhist.

00:06:47.710 --> 00:06:49.700 align:middle line:84%
So I don't reify
silence, although there

00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:50.500 align:middle line:90%
is a famous thing.

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:52.690 align:middle line:84%
There is a sutra
that I translated

00:06:52.690 --> 00:06:55.120 align:middle line:84%
called "The Holy
Teaching of Vimalakirti."

00:06:55.120 --> 00:06:59.470 align:middle line:10%
And in that, in chapter 9,
there is a very famous point

00:06:59.470 --> 00:07:02.140 align:middle line:10%
where, after asking 32
different people what

00:07:02.140 --> 00:07:04.240 align:middle line:10%
their view of the nature
of ultimate reality was,

00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:06.470 align:middle line:10%
the highest reality
type of question--

00:07:06.470 --> 00:07:07.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:07:07.270 --> 00:07:09.220 align:middle line:84%
>> --they then turned
to Vimalakirti himself,

00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.570 align:middle line:84%
who was presiding,
and they say, well,

00:07:11.570 --> 00:07:13.593 align:middle line:84%
we've all said what
we wanted to say.

00:07:13.593 --> 00:07:15.010 align:middle line:84%
What do you think,
Vimalakirti, is

00:07:15.010 --> 00:07:16.570 align:middle line:90%
the highest nature of reality?

00:07:16.570 --> 00:07:21.640 align:middle line:84%
At which point, Vimalakirti
remained silent.

00:07:21.640 --> 00:07:24.480 align:middle line:84%
And they call that the lion's
roar of the Vimalakirti

00:07:24.480 --> 00:07:25.650 align:middle line:90%
silence.

00:07:25.650 --> 00:07:29.080 align:middle line:84%
And in a way, they consider
it sort of the most profound.

00:07:29.080 --> 00:07:29.890 align:middle line:90%
It's sort of this--

00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:32.460 align:middle line:84%
But now, in the
same sutra, there's

00:07:32.460 --> 00:07:35.550 align:middle line:84%
a goddess who comes out of
the woodwork at one point, who

00:07:35.550 --> 00:07:37.260 align:middle line:90%
is a very enlightened goddess.

00:07:37.260 --> 00:07:39.420 align:middle line:84%
And she's teasing
the different monks.

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And at one time, in teasing
this one head monk, who's

00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:43.440 align:middle line:84%
a very enlightened
head monk, she

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:47.100 align:middle line:84%
asked him, well, how long
have you been enlightened,

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.135 align:middle line:90%
by the way, type of thing.

00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:50.760 align:middle line:84%
Because he's asking
her some questions.

00:07:50.760 --> 00:07:52.530 align:middle line:84%
And she says, well, how long
have you been enlightened,

00:07:52.530 --> 00:07:53.670 align:middle line:90%
she says.

00:07:53.670 --> 00:07:56.790 align:middle line:84%
And then he doesn't
say anything.

00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:59.070 align:middle line:84%
So then she doesn't accept
that as something profound.

00:07:59.070 --> 00:08:02.252 align:middle line:84%
And she says, excuse me,
Venerable Shariputra,

00:08:02.252 --> 00:08:03.210 align:middle line:90%
I asked you a question.

00:08:03.210 --> 00:08:04.992 align:middle line:90%
It's your turn to respond.

00:08:04.992 --> 00:08:07.200 align:middle line:84%
Like, how come you're not
answering when I asked you,

00:08:07.200 --> 00:08:08.220 align:middle line:84%
how long have you
been enlightened?

00:08:08.220 --> 00:08:09.360 align:middle line:84%
You just indicated something
about enlightenment.

00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:11.068 align:middle line:84%
Well, how long have
you been enlightened?

00:08:11.068 --> 00:08:12.693 align:middle line:84%
So he says, well, I
didn't say anything

00:08:12.693 --> 00:08:14.850 align:middle line:84%
because I thought that,
really, you can't indicated

00:08:14.850 --> 00:08:16.890 align:middle line:90%
enlightenment with any words.

00:08:16.890 --> 00:08:20.010 align:middle line:84%
She said, oh, Venerable
Shariputra, do not say that.

00:08:20.010 --> 00:08:22.150 align:middle line:84%
Do not try to point to
enlightenment by silence,

00:08:22.150 --> 00:08:23.580 align:middle line:90%
she said.

00:08:23.580 --> 00:08:27.030 align:middle line:84%
The nature of words is neither
external, nor internal,

00:08:27.030 --> 00:08:28.740 align:middle line:90%
nor somewhere in between.

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:32.039 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, enlightenment is
neither external, nor internal,

00:08:32.039 --> 00:08:33.510 align:middle line:90%
nor somewhere in between.

00:08:33.510 --> 00:08:37.530 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, the nature of
words is itself enlightenment.

00:08:37.530 --> 00:08:39.770 align:middle line:84%
Enlightenment itself
is the nature of words.

00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:41.200 align:middle line:90%
So the poor guy was like--

00:08:41.200 --> 00:08:42.659 align:middle line:90%
he was a little bit--

