00:34:24.705 --> 00:34:25.580 align:middle line:10%
How are the Tibetan--

00:34:25.580 --> 00:34:28.659 align:middle line:10%
>> They-- well,
nowadays, in exile,

00:34:28.659 --> 00:34:31.090 align:middle line:10%
they're chosen by election.

00:34:31.090 --> 00:34:33.010 align:middle line:10%
And they have their
own electoral process

00:34:33.010 --> 00:34:35.860 align:middle line:10%
because they have developed
a working constitution,

00:34:35.860 --> 00:34:38.880 align:middle line:10%
and a parliament,
and a supreme court,

00:34:38.880 --> 00:34:40.780 align:middle line:10%
modeled on a combination
of the Indian,

00:34:40.780 --> 00:34:42.568 align:middle line:10%
the British, and the
American systems,

00:34:42.568 --> 00:34:44.110 align:middle line:10%
which they hope to
implement in Tibet

00:34:44.110 --> 00:34:46.630 align:middle line:10%
if they ever get true
self-rule in Tibet.

00:34:46.630 --> 00:34:48.130 align:middle line:84%
In Tibet, of course,
they're just--

00:34:48.130 --> 00:34:49.210 align:middle line:90%
the ones who work--

00:34:49.210 --> 00:34:51.088 align:middle line:84%
mainly, Chinese
run all the offices

00:34:51.088 --> 00:34:52.130 align:middle line:90%
at all the higher levels.

00:34:52.130 --> 00:34:54.190 align:middle line:84%
But they have
Tibetan collaborators

00:34:54.190 --> 00:34:57.023 align:middle line:84%
who are appointed to the lower
levels of their bureaucracy.

00:34:57.023 --> 00:34:58.690 align:middle line:84%
So they don't have
any freedom in Tibet.

00:34:58.690 --> 00:35:01.180 align:middle line:84%
And you know, Communism
has no real elections.

00:35:01.180 --> 00:35:02.690 align:middle line:90%
The party controls everything.

00:35:02.690 --> 00:35:04.198 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:35:04.198 --> 00:35:05.990 align:middle line:84%
>> But in ancient time
in Tibet, of course,

00:35:05.990 --> 00:35:07.990 align:middle line:84%
they had a funny
way of leadership,

00:35:07.990 --> 00:35:10.300 align:middle line:84%
where you had to have many
lifetimes of on-the-job

00:35:10.300 --> 00:35:11.420 align:middle line:90%
training.

00:35:11.420 --> 00:35:12.820 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you
didn't run for election.

00:35:12.820 --> 00:35:14.710 align:middle line:84%
You just had to prove that,
well, I've already been

00:35:14.710 --> 00:35:15.700 align:middle line:90%
sheriff for five lifetimes.

00:35:15.700 --> 00:35:16.160 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:16.420 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:35:16.420 --> 00:35:18.482 align:middle line:84%
>> I practiced, and now
I'll be a good sheriff.

00:35:18.482 --> 00:35:20.440 align:middle line:84%
And then people say, OK,
he's the reincarnation

00:35:20.440 --> 00:35:20.980 align:middle line:90%
of the sheriff.

00:35:20.980 --> 00:35:22.522 align:middle line:84%
Let's let him go
back to the sheriff.

00:35:22.522 --> 00:35:24.340 align:middle line:84%
So ironically,
although they didn't

00:35:24.340 --> 00:35:27.160 align:middle line:84%
have an electoral system,
they had one step, certainly,

00:35:27.160 --> 00:35:32.003 align:middle line:84%
more towards the democratic than
the dynastic, imperial system,

00:35:32.003 --> 00:35:33.670 align:middle line:84%
where you just-- your
children inherited

00:35:33.670 --> 00:35:35.110 align:middle line:90%
the throne type of thing.

00:35:35.110 --> 00:35:39.160 align:middle line:84%
Because those reincarnated
lamas, like the Dalai Lamas,

00:35:39.160 --> 00:35:42.670 align:middle line:84%
all but one of them were born in
lower class, peasant families.

00:35:42.670 --> 00:35:45.040 align:middle line:84%
Only one was born as an
aristocratic and noble family,

00:35:45.040 --> 00:35:46.480 align:middle line:90%
out of 14.

00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:47.378 align:middle line:90%
The rest were all--

00:35:47.378 --> 00:35:49.420 align:middle line:84%
and they were born in
different regions of Tibet.

00:35:49.420 --> 00:35:53.330 align:middle line:84%
So it was just like log cabin
to White House, Hope, Arkansas

00:35:53.330 --> 00:35:54.170 align:middle line:90%
to White House.

00:35:54.170 --> 00:35:56.650 align:middle line:84%
It operated in a way
of effectively giving

00:35:56.650 --> 00:35:59.302 align:middle line:84%
a kind of turnover and social
mobility within the system,

00:35:59.302 --> 00:36:01.510 align:middle line:84%
but without, of course, the
modern electoral process.

00:36:01.510 --> 00:36:03.580 align:middle line:84%
Because they didn't
have universal literacy.

00:36:03.580 --> 00:36:05.830 align:middle line:84%
And they didn't
have voting boxes,

00:36:05.830 --> 00:36:07.730 align:middle line:84%
electronic communication,
this kind of thing.

00:36:07.730 --> 00:36:09.438 align:middle line:84%
But they hope to have
that in the future.

00:36:09.438 --> 00:36:11.060 align:middle line:90%
And they hope to have democracy.

00:36:11.060 --> 00:36:12.700 align:middle line:84%
Although I'm a
little bit concerned

00:36:12.700 --> 00:36:15.580 align:middle line:84%
that there's a complexity
there because one

00:36:15.580 --> 00:36:18.280 align:middle line:84%
of our aspects of
democracy is secularism,

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:21.520 align:middle line:84%
of American democracy, you know,
separation of church and state.

00:36:21.520 --> 00:36:22.950 align:middle line:90%
But we have interpreted that--

00:36:22.950 --> 00:36:26.265 align:middle line:84%
that was meant to protect
different religious movements,

00:36:26.265 --> 00:36:28.390 align:middle line:84%
minority religious movements,
from being persecuted

00:36:28.390 --> 00:36:30.730 align:middle line:84%
by some majority religion
that would dominate

00:36:30.730 --> 00:36:34.450 align:middle line:84%
the state because of our
ancestors' experience

00:36:34.450 --> 00:36:36.580 align:middle line:90%
of persecution in Europe.

00:36:36.580 --> 00:36:38.440 align:middle line:84%
But that was not
necessarily meant

00:36:38.440 --> 00:36:40.180 align:middle line:84%
to keep all spiritual
perspectives out

00:36:40.180 --> 00:36:43.060 align:middle line:84%
of the educational system and
out of the governmental system

00:36:43.060 --> 00:36:47.410 align:middle line:84%
and sort of have a ethic of
money, an ethic of materialism.

00:36:47.410 --> 00:36:49.600 align:middle line:84%
But that's what it's
resulted in, you see.

00:36:49.600 --> 00:36:53.230 align:middle line:84%
So there must be a middle
way between secularism

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:56.620 align:middle line:84%
that just leads to
materialism and some sort

00:36:56.620 --> 00:37:00.010 align:middle line:84%
of religious dominance that is
one particular religion, where

00:37:00.010 --> 00:37:04.720 align:middle line:84%
you have a spiritual infusion
in the ethic of the state

00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:06.490 align:middle line:90%
and the ethic of the people.

00:37:06.490 --> 00:37:07.648 align:middle line:90%
You preserve that.

00:37:07.648 --> 00:37:09.440 align:middle line:84%
And yet, you don't
allow any one religion--

00:37:09.440 --> 00:37:11.148 align:middle line:84%
you preserve pluralism
on the other hand,

00:37:11.148 --> 00:37:13.370 align:middle line:84%
and don't allow one religion
to persecute any other.

00:37:13.370 --> 00:37:15.490 align:middle line:84%
And I hope that
Tibet will rethink

00:37:15.490 --> 00:37:17.770 align:middle line:84%
its imitation of
Western democracy

00:37:17.770 --> 00:37:19.750 align:middle line:84%
and come up with
more of a middle way.

00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:21.400 align:middle line:90%
Do you know I mean?

00:37:21.400 --> 00:37:23.600 align:middle line:90%
Without having an inquisition.

00:37:23.600 --> 00:37:27.310 align:middle line:84%
But although, because Buddhism
is a less dogmatic religion

00:37:27.310 --> 00:37:31.420 align:middle line:84%
than monotheistic religions,
not just Western ones, but even

00:37:31.420 --> 00:37:33.820 align:middle line:84%
Indian or eastern
monotheistic religions,

00:37:33.820 --> 00:37:37.270 align:middle line:84%
because it-- but they don't
believe in any superboss deity.

00:37:37.270 --> 00:37:40.570 align:middle line:84%
They believe in the
deities of love.

00:37:40.570 --> 00:37:42.400 align:middle line:90%
And there's a few naughty ones.

00:37:42.400 --> 00:37:44.920 align:middle line:84%
But they don't believe
in one big boss.

00:37:44.920 --> 00:37:47.260 align:middle line:84%
So therefore, they tend
to be less sort of--

00:37:47.260 --> 00:37:48.938 align:middle line:84%
they never had an
Inquisition, where

00:37:48.938 --> 00:37:50.480 align:middle line:84%
they pulled out your
thumbs until you

00:37:50.480 --> 00:37:52.090 align:middle line:90%
proclaimed this or that dogma.

00:37:52.090 --> 00:37:53.950 align:middle line:90%
They didn't do that in Buddhism.

00:37:53.950 --> 00:37:57.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Are you optimistic
about the future of Tibet?

00:37:57.250 --> 00:37:58.650 align:middle line:90%
>> I am.

00:37:58.650 --> 00:37:59.450 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how.

00:37:59.450 --> 00:38:03.350 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] It's such a dire
situation at the moment.

00:38:03.350 --> 00:38:05.090 align:middle line:90%
But in fact, I am.

00:38:05.090 --> 00:38:08.985 align:middle line:84%
And not only for mystical
reasons, let's say,

00:38:08.985 --> 00:38:10.450 align:middle line:90%
because I'm fairly weak.

00:38:10.450 --> 00:38:12.650 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I mentally would
like to be more like that,

00:38:12.650 --> 00:38:16.130 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not that strong in
that area, by being too left

00:38:16.130 --> 00:38:19.370 align:middle line:84%
brain and rationalistic, the
way I was educated, but really,

00:38:19.370 --> 00:38:22.490 align:middle line:84%
from my view of this
socioeconomic, technological

00:38:22.490 --> 00:38:24.150 align:middle line:90%
state of the planet.

00:38:24.150 --> 00:38:25.670 align:middle line:10%
In other words,
the British didn't

00:38:25.670 --> 00:38:27.820 align:middle line:10%
give up their empire,
or the French Algeria,

00:38:27.820 --> 00:38:29.900 align:middle line:10%
the British India, the
Portuguese, the Congo,

00:38:29.900 --> 00:38:32.150 align:middle line:10%
whatever-- they didn't give
these up because they were

00:38:32.150 --> 00:38:33.830 align:middle line:10%
all a bunch of bodhisattvas.

00:38:33.830 --> 00:38:36.440 align:middle line:84%
The Russians didn't give up
all of their possessions,

00:38:36.440 --> 00:38:38.390 align:middle line:84%
their empire, you
know, the Soviet Union,

00:38:38.390 --> 00:38:42.050 align:middle line:84%
because they were suddenly
sainted or enlightened.

00:38:42.050 --> 00:38:46.460 align:middle line:84%
They did it because the
military industrial control

00:38:46.460 --> 00:38:49.910 align:middle line:84%
of huge territory is
not cost effective

00:38:49.910 --> 00:38:51.570 align:middle line:90%
in the modern economy.

00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:53.410 align:middle line:90%
Look at the case of China.

00:38:53.410 --> 00:38:57.320 align:middle line:84%
The Chinese who tried to control
a big territory and maintain

00:38:57.320 --> 00:39:00.680 align:middle line:84%
an imperium in Mongolia,
Manchuria, Xiangyang,

00:39:00.680 --> 00:39:04.175 align:middle line:84%
and Tibet, since their
liberation in 1950, 1949,

00:39:04.175 --> 00:39:06.410 align:middle line:90%
the so-called liberation--

00:39:06.410 --> 00:39:08.487 align:middle line:84%
they are still
totally poor, really,

00:39:08.487 --> 00:39:10.070 align:middle line:84%
except for all this
foreign investment

00:39:10.070 --> 00:39:14.270 align:middle line:84%
lately, due to the fantasies of
Western, naive business people.

00:39:14.270 --> 00:39:17.510 align:middle line:84%
But Hong Kong,
with no territory,

00:39:17.510 --> 00:39:21.380 align:middle line:84%
Taiwan, with a little island,
Singapore Chinese community,

00:39:21.380 --> 00:39:24.590 align:middle line:84%
Indonesian Chinese community,
Malaysian Chinese community,

00:39:24.590 --> 00:39:27.380 align:middle line:84%
the US overseas
Chinese community,

00:39:27.380 --> 00:39:30.890 align:middle line:84%
have prospered mightily
with no territory,

00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:35.240 align:middle line:84%
just by industrial creativity,
consumer savvy, marketing

00:39:35.240 --> 00:39:37.430 align:middle line:90%
brilliance, inventions, genius.

00:39:37.430 --> 00:39:39.530 align:middle line:84%
That's the way the
world economy is.

00:39:39.530 --> 00:39:42.740 align:middle line:84%
The idea that you pay some
troops, millions of them,

00:39:42.740 --> 00:39:45.380 align:middle line:84%
some salary to go and
suppress people's creativity

00:39:45.380 --> 00:39:49.370 align:middle line:84%
so you can say I own the land
is stupid in the modern economy.

00:39:49.370 --> 00:39:51.770 align:middle line:84%
It leads, eventually,
to-- in the case of Tibet,

00:39:51.770 --> 00:39:54.993 align:middle line:84%
because of the religiosity and
non-violence of the Tibetans,

00:39:54.993 --> 00:39:56.660 align:middle line:84%
they haven't been
blowing up the bridges

00:39:56.660 --> 00:39:59.120 align:middle line:84%
all the time, like in
Afghanistan or somewhere,

00:39:59.120 --> 00:40:01.550 align:middle line:84%
or in Vietnam, because of
the particular intensity

00:40:01.550 --> 00:40:03.710 align:middle line:84%
of the non-violence of
the Tibetan ideology.

00:40:03.710 --> 00:40:05.540 align:middle line:84%
But eventually, they
will if this goes on.

00:40:05.540 --> 00:40:07.682 align:middle line:84%
The Dalai Lama will not
be able to restrain them.

00:40:07.682 --> 00:40:09.890 align:middle line:84%
And the point is they haven't
done anything creative.

00:40:09.890 --> 00:40:11.120 align:middle line:90%
They haven't been allowed to.

00:40:11.120 --> 00:40:13.310 align:middle line:84%
Whereas Tibetans in exile
have thrived and prospered

00:40:13.310 --> 00:40:14.630 align:middle line:90%
with their creativity.

00:40:14.630 --> 00:40:17.180 align:middle line:84%
And Tibet could be
a gem economically

00:40:17.180 --> 00:40:18.950 align:middle line:90%
if China wasn't suppressing it.

00:40:18.950 --> 00:40:22.070 align:middle line:84%
It could be a fabulous tourist
destination, a fantastic health

00:40:22.070 --> 00:40:22.940 align:middle line:90%
industry.

00:40:22.940 --> 00:40:25.370 align:middle line:84%
The Tibetans would make their
place as beautiful and as

00:40:25.370 --> 00:40:27.470 align:middle line:84%
adorable and as cute as
when they come and give

00:40:27.470 --> 00:40:29.450 align:middle line:84%
a teaching here or
make a mandala there

00:40:29.450 --> 00:40:31.160 align:middle line:84%
or do chants in
the other places,

00:40:31.160 --> 00:40:32.670 align:middle line:90%
or have shops out in the street.

00:40:32.670 --> 00:40:34.128 align:middle line:84%
They're incredibly
creative people.

00:40:34.128 --> 00:40:35.910 align:middle line:84%
They're the Swiss
people of Asia.

00:40:35.910 --> 00:40:38.910 align:middle line:84%
And so, the modern
economy, it is creative.

00:40:38.910 --> 00:40:40.580 align:middle line:84%
I have a friend who
is a Chinologist who

00:40:40.580 --> 00:40:42.980 align:middle line:84%
had his eyes open finally
learning about the "minority"

00:40:42.980 --> 00:40:44.660 align:middle line:84%
quote-unquote
situation in China,

00:40:44.660 --> 00:40:45.980 align:middle line:90%
the Tibetans and everybody.

00:40:45.980 --> 00:40:50.058 align:middle line:84%
And he had a great thing when
his PRC people would say, oh,

00:40:50.058 --> 00:40:51.350 align:middle line:90%
it takes us so long to develop.

00:40:51.350 --> 00:40:52.830 align:middle line:90%
We're so big.

00:40:52.830 --> 00:40:54.080 align:middle line:90%
Be patient with us.

00:40:54.080 --> 00:40:54.960 align:middle line:90%
We are third world.

00:40:54.960 --> 00:40:55.760 align:middle line:90%
We're so big.

00:40:55.760 --> 00:40:58.340 align:middle line:84%
And he would say, guys,
take a look at Hong Kong.

00:40:58.340 --> 00:41:00.250 align:middle line:84%
If bigness is a
problem, get small.

00:41:00.250 --> 00:41:02.960 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:41:02.960 --> 00:41:05.240 align:middle line:84%
>> So for that reason,
I'm really optimistic.

00:41:05.240 --> 00:41:06.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Excellent.

00:41:06.080 --> 00:41:09.980 align:middle line:84%
>> The military, and the PLA
and these people in China,

00:41:09.980 --> 00:41:12.230 align:middle line:84%
People's Liberation Army,
they're making money ripping

00:41:12.230 --> 00:41:15.200 align:middle line:84%
off the trees in
Tibet, some minerals.

00:41:15.200 --> 00:41:17.340 align:middle line:84%
And they have salaries
for their soldiers.

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:18.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's a big
campaign for them.

00:41:18.950 --> 00:41:20.310 align:middle line:90%
It's a basic minus.

00:41:20.310 --> 00:41:23.690 align:middle line:84%
It's a deficit at this stage
in the national exchequer

00:41:23.690 --> 00:41:24.620 align:middle line:90%
if somebody--

00:41:24.620 --> 00:41:27.770 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] or Jiang Zemin,
as economists from the coast,

00:41:27.770 --> 00:41:29.540 align:middle line:84%
from Shanghai,
make a calculation,

00:41:29.540 --> 00:41:32.240 align:middle line:84%
they are losing money on
Tibet, although individual PLA

00:41:32.240 --> 00:41:34.003 align:middle line:90%
businesses are making money.

00:41:34.003 --> 00:41:35.420 align:middle line:84%
But the overall
Chinese people are

00:41:35.420 --> 00:41:38.135 align:middle line:84%
losing money for this adventure
of theirs in the Himalayas.

00:41:38.135 --> 00:41:40.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:41:40.270 --> 00:41:41.660 align:middle line:90%
>> So that's why I'm optimistic.

00:41:41.660 --> 00:41:44.405 align:middle line:84%
Because it's just not cost
effective to be nasty.

00:41:44.405 --> 00:41:45.205 align:middle line:90%
It's too expensive.

00:41:45.205 --> 00:41:46.700 align:middle line:90%
>> It's not.

00:41:46.700 --> 00:41:49.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Besides being not
nice, it's too expensive.

00:41:49.670 --> 00:41:52.010 align:middle line:84%
>> When people read
your most recent book,

00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.240 align:middle line:84%
called "Circling the
Sacred Mountain"--

00:41:54.240 --> 00:41:55.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:41:55.220 --> 00:41:58.160 align:middle line:10%
>> --what would you want them
to know, to come away with?

00:41:58.160 --> 00:42:00.380 align:middle line:10%
>> What I would want
them to come away with,

00:42:00.380 --> 00:42:03.230 align:middle line:10%
besides a pleasant walk in
the mountains in this magic

00:42:03.230 --> 00:42:05.990 align:middle line:10%
mountain, sacred not only
to Buddhists, but to Hindus,

00:42:05.990 --> 00:42:07.910 align:middle line:10%
to Jains, to Bonpos--

00:42:07.910 --> 00:42:10.790 align:middle line:10%
and I met a couple of
Japanese Christian monks

00:42:10.790 --> 00:42:12.830 align:middle line:10%
who were circumnambulating
when I was there.

00:42:12.830 --> 00:42:14.840 align:middle line:84%
I think it's one of the
holiest mountains in the world.

00:42:14.840 --> 00:42:16.310 align:middle line:84%
There's something
magical about it.

00:42:16.310 --> 00:42:21.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't it said that when
you circle that mountain,

00:42:21.530 --> 00:42:22.650 align:middle line:90%
your sins are eradicated.

00:42:22.650 --> 00:42:23.450 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:42:23.450 --> 00:42:23.890 align:middle line:90%
>> That's one of the--

00:42:23.890 --> 00:42:25.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's a general
pilgrimage thing, know,

00:42:25.460 --> 00:42:26.920 align:middle line:90%
lure in the same kind of thing.

00:42:26.920 --> 00:42:27.950 align:middle line:90%
It's an Asian lure.

00:42:27.950 --> 00:42:28.950 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a lovely notion.

00:42:28.950 --> 00:42:29.780 align:middle line:90%
>> It is a lovely notion.

00:42:29.780 --> 00:42:31.530 align:middle line:84%
It's a rather harsh
mountain to get around

00:42:31.530 --> 00:42:34.380 align:middle line:84%
because the high pass going
around is 18,600 feet.

00:42:34.380 --> 00:42:35.180 align:middle line:90%
>> [GASPS]

00:42:35.180 --> 00:42:36.860 align:middle line:90%
>> So it's quite a hike.

00:42:36.860 --> 00:42:39.370 align:middle line:84%
But that's also kind of macho
and challenging and nice.

00:42:39.370 --> 00:42:40.170 align:middle line:90%
It's not dangerous.

00:42:40.170 --> 00:42:41.160 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
climb with ropes.

00:42:41.160 --> 00:42:42.278 align:middle line:90%
But it's just a hard walk.

00:42:42.278 --> 00:42:43.320 align:middle line:90%
>> But it's hard to get--

00:42:43.320 --> 00:42:44.320 align:middle line:84%
>> For one who's not
used to the climate.

00:42:44.320 --> 00:42:44.900 align:middle line:90%
>> --air.

00:42:44.900 --> 00:42:45.700 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:42:45.700 --> 00:42:48.350 align:middle line:84%
>> But I would like them
to enjoy the vista of this

00:42:48.350 --> 00:42:50.900 align:middle line:84%
wonderful-- and see the world
from this sort of sacred holy

00:42:50.900 --> 00:42:51.200 align:middle line:90%
place.

00:42:51.200 --> 00:42:52.310 align:middle line:90%
That I would like.

00:42:52.310 --> 00:42:54.393 align:middle line:10%
And the other thing I would
like them to come away

00:42:54.393 --> 00:42:57.650 align:middle line:10%
with about Buddhism is
that Buddhism is not just

00:42:57.650 --> 00:43:00.830 align:middle line:10%
some exotic, strange,
mysterious thing that is simply

00:43:00.830 --> 00:43:03.918 align:middle line:10%
meditation, or simply some
sort of beads, or simply

00:43:03.918 --> 00:43:05.960 align:middle line:10%
some sort of magical
mantra, something like that,

00:43:05.960 --> 00:43:07.310 align:middle line:10%
or some lama.

00:43:07.310 --> 00:43:12.020 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism, basically,
is the turning away

00:43:12.020 --> 00:43:15.200 align:middle line:84%
from self-obsession
and self-infatuation

00:43:15.200 --> 00:43:19.850 align:middle line:84%
and self-preoccupation, and
turning towards altruism,

00:43:19.850 --> 00:43:22.280 align:middle line:84%
and other sensitivity,
and lovingness

00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:25.520 align:middle line:84%
and compassionateness to
others, and finding happiness

00:43:25.520 --> 00:43:28.910 align:middle line:84%
through the happiness of others,
instead of being constantly

00:43:28.910 --> 00:43:32.030 align:middle line:84%
satisfied by focusing
on how happy you are,

00:43:32.030 --> 00:43:34.160 align:middle line:90%
which will never be good enough.

00:43:34.160 --> 00:43:35.792 align:middle line:84%
When you focus on
how happy you are,

00:43:35.792 --> 00:43:37.250 align:middle line:84%
even when you're
having fun, you're

00:43:37.250 --> 00:43:38.875 align:middle line:84%
going to be dissatisfied
because you'll

00:43:38.875 --> 00:43:40.630 align:middle line:84%
remember you had more
fun another time,

00:43:40.630 --> 00:43:43.700 align:middle line:84%
or it could be better this way
or something better that way.

00:43:43.700 --> 00:43:45.838 align:middle line:84%
So that is really
what Buddhism is.

00:43:45.838 --> 00:43:47.255 align:middle line:84%
You know, so many
people, I think,

00:43:47.255 --> 00:43:49.160 align:middle line:90%
think about it negatively.

00:43:49.160 --> 00:43:51.410 align:middle line:84%
They think it's just some
running away from the world.

00:43:51.410 --> 00:43:53.090 align:middle line:84%
And when they think
they're positive,

00:43:53.090 --> 00:43:54.548 align:middle line:84%
they think it's
some sort of escape

00:43:54.548 --> 00:43:57.720 align:middle line:84%
into some meditative state,
away from their problems.

00:43:57.720 --> 00:44:01.400 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, what Buddhism is
the same thing that humanism

00:44:01.400 --> 00:44:03.470 align:middle line:84%
wants, the same thing
that Christianity wants,

00:44:03.470 --> 00:44:05.540 align:middle line:84%
that Judaism wants,
that Islam wants,

00:44:05.540 --> 00:44:07.880 align:middle line:84%
Hinduism wants, which
is to help people

00:44:07.880 --> 00:44:11.725 align:middle line:84%
find more happiness by being
less selfish basically.

00:44:11.725 --> 00:44:13.100 align:middle line:84%
And I give a
teaching there which

00:44:13.100 --> 00:44:15.350 align:middle line:84%
I gave to the people
on the mountain, which

00:44:15.350 --> 00:44:18.710 align:middle line:84%
comes from ninth
century Tibet and Bengal

00:44:18.710 --> 00:44:21.450 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, some of the great
Indian masters of that time,

00:44:21.450 --> 00:44:24.140 align:middle line:84%
in a period when India
was under invasion

00:44:24.140 --> 00:44:26.730 align:middle line:84%
from various steppe, nomadic
people who were laying waste

00:44:26.730 --> 00:44:27.530 align:middle line:90%
to India.

00:44:27.530 --> 00:44:30.200 align:middle line:84%
So it was a very,
very dangerous time

00:44:30.200 --> 00:44:33.590 align:middle line:84%
for everybody, which is called
"The Blade Wheel of Mind

00:44:33.590 --> 00:44:34.437 align:middle line:90%
Reform."

00:44:34.437 --> 00:44:35.270 align:middle line:90%
>> The Blade Wheel--

00:44:35.270 --> 00:44:37.010 align:middle line:84%
>> "The Blade Wheel of
Mind-- the blade wheel is one

00:44:37.010 --> 00:44:38.450 align:middle line:84%
of the things that the
ninjas throw, you know?

00:44:38.450 --> 00:44:40.550 align:middle line:84%
It's a spinning knife with
the blades on all sides.

00:44:40.550 --> 00:44:41.350 align:middle line:90%
>> I see, yes.

00:44:41.350 --> 00:44:43.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Like a roto-rooter
or something.

00:44:43.460 --> 00:44:46.280 align:middle line:84%
And "The Blade Wheel of Mind
Reform" is like a very fierce--

00:44:46.280 --> 00:44:49.550 align:middle line:84%
it's a very fierce image
of using a wheel like that

00:44:49.550 --> 00:44:52.820 align:middle line:84%
to conquer the inner
enemy of selfishness

00:44:52.820 --> 00:44:56.810 align:middle line:84%
and to reform the mind from
being self-inverted and focused

00:44:56.810 --> 00:44:59.660 align:middle line:84%
on itself to opening into
the world and realizing

00:44:59.660 --> 00:45:01.395 align:middle line:84%
what a marvelous,
magical place it is.

00:45:01.395 --> 00:45:03.020 align:middle line:84%
So that's what I
would really like them

00:45:03.020 --> 00:45:04.640 align:middle line:90%
to come away with in that book.

00:45:04.640 --> 00:45:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And I think I was inspired
to do that because being

00:45:08.030 --> 00:45:10.670 align:middle line:84%
in that place of
that mountain, you

00:45:10.670 --> 00:45:13.632 align:middle line:84%
didn't feel like a beating
around the bush, you know,

00:45:13.632 --> 00:45:15.590 align:middle line:84%
because you're in this
amazing place in nature.

00:45:15.590 --> 00:45:19.640 align:middle line:84%
I swear I'm not that
good an environmentalist.

00:45:19.640 --> 00:45:21.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm not psychic or anything.

00:45:21.840 --> 00:45:24.110 align:middle line:84%
But it was like when I
woke up the first morning

00:45:24.110 --> 00:45:25.130 align:middle line:90%
in that place--

00:45:25.130 --> 00:45:27.500 align:middle line:84%
and the surface of it,
the little town near it

00:45:27.500 --> 00:45:30.058 align:middle line:84%
is terribly grubby,
Chinese garrison.

00:45:30.058 --> 00:45:32.600 align:middle line:84%
You know, the Tibetan pilgrims
are sort of suppressed and so.

00:45:32.600 --> 00:45:34.870 align:middle line:90%
On and it's broken glass.

00:45:34.870 --> 00:45:39.050 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you know, underfed
dogs, it's not that cute.

00:45:39.050 --> 00:45:41.060 align:middle line:84%
But somehow, the whole
land, and the earth,

00:45:41.060 --> 00:45:43.715 align:middle line:84%
and the mountain, the ice,
was all alive and glowing.

00:45:43.715 --> 00:45:46.160 align:middle line:84%
And I've never seen
nature like that.

00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:48.620 align:middle line:90%
And I was totally surprised.

00:45:48.620 --> 00:45:49.490 align:middle line:90%
I was like--

00:45:49.490 --> 00:45:50.960 align:middle line:84%
I was embarrassed when
I first got there.

00:45:50.960 --> 00:45:51.860 align:middle line:84%
I thought oh, what
a grubby place.

00:45:51.860 --> 00:45:53.270 align:middle line:90%
I brought all these people here.

00:45:53.270 --> 00:45:55.520 align:middle line:84%
It's just another dumb place
that some pilgrims thinks

00:45:55.520 --> 00:45:57.780 align:middle line:84%
is great, but it's
just a bunch of rocks.

00:45:57.780 --> 00:45:59.630 align:middle line:84%
I woke up in the
morning, and the rocks

00:45:59.630 --> 00:46:03.180 align:middle line:84%
were dancing and
singing and glowing.

00:46:03.180 --> 00:46:04.618 align:middle line:90%
And I couldn't believe it.

00:46:04.618 --> 00:46:06.660 align:middle line:84%
And then everybody who
was there the whole time--

00:46:06.660 --> 00:46:08.000 align:middle line:90%
And another property of Mt.

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:09.920 align:middle line:84%
Kailash-- anybody
who goes there,

00:46:09.920 --> 00:46:13.520 align:middle line:84%
they should take pictures of
their ancestors, any departed

00:46:13.520 --> 00:46:15.950 align:middle line:90%
loved one, lock of hair.

00:46:15.950 --> 00:46:18.110 align:middle line:84%
Tibetans do that, these
different sort of-- they're

00:46:18.110 --> 00:46:20.240 align:middle line:84%
not really graveyards,
they're commemoration yards,

00:46:20.240 --> 00:46:22.370 align:middle line:84%
which look a little
bit like junk heaps.

00:46:22.370 --> 00:46:25.400 align:middle line:84%
But people put
articles of clothing.

00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:26.900 align:middle line:84%
Because when you
go there, you start

00:46:26.900 --> 00:46:30.410 align:middle line:84%
to think of all of your roots
and the past generations.

00:46:30.410 --> 00:46:32.600 align:middle line:84%
And the Tibetans
believe that if you

00:46:32.600 --> 00:46:35.090 align:middle line:84%
make prayers for even
people in the past,

00:46:35.090 --> 00:46:38.350 align:middle line:84%
the power of the deities
of that place is so great,

00:46:38.350 --> 00:46:41.000 align:middle line:84%
they can sort of go and help
people in the past even,

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:42.530 align:middle line:90%
change even a negative past.

00:46:42.530 --> 00:46:44.700 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of a miraculous
thing, you know.

00:46:44.700 --> 00:46:46.010 align:middle line:90%
And it's very, very moving.

00:46:46.010 --> 00:46:47.870 align:middle line:90%
It really is a moving place.

00:46:47.870 --> 00:46:51.020 align:middle line:84%
So I hope everyone will enjoy
that when they read that book.

00:46:51.020 --> 00:46:53.990 align:middle line:84%
>> "Circling the Sacred
Mountain," I think they will.

00:46:53.990 --> 00:46:55.920 align:middle line:90%
I thank you for all your books.

00:46:55.920 --> 00:46:56.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:46:56.720 --> 00:46:59.510 align:middle line:84%
>> I thank you for your
extraordinary words,

00:46:59.510 --> 00:47:01.660 align:middle line:90%
your compassion in the world.

00:47:01.660 --> 00:47:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And mostly, I thank you
for being a noisy Buddhist.

00:47:03.930 --> 00:47:06.330 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS] Thank you very much.

